        <h1>history of maratha empire</h1>
        <p>The<b>maratha empire</b> was a dominant Indian power that shaped the subcontinent's history between the 17<sup>th</sup> and 19<sup>th</sup> centuries. Founded in the western Deccan by <strong>chatrapati shivaji maharaj in 1674</strong>, it rose by <ins>challaenging the Mughal and Bijapur Saltanat</ins>. Eventually expanding into a vast confederacy, the Marathas were the primary force that dismantled Mughal dominance before falling to the British East India Company in 1818.</p>
